{"title": "Text-book of Assaying", "description": "This is a formal but relaxed text covering assaying techniques for most of the substances which are mined. As the authors say: \"At first our intention was to supply a description of those substances only which have a commercial value, but on consideration we have added short accounts of the rarer elements...\"<br /><br />The book's early chapters are wide-ranging, describing the general theory of assaying and a range of methods and reagents, with the later chapters describing analytical methods for different groups of metals and for some non-metallic substances. It includes many excellent illustrations of the scientific method, demonstrating the effects of changing the parameters of many of the assay techniques.<br /><br />It was first published in 1889; this edition in 1904.<br /><br />[The reader has omitted some mathematical examples, tables of data and descriptions of figures, where their inclusion would seem to over-complicate the text; and has attempted to describe many of the pieces of apparatus which are illustrated.] (Introduction by Peter Yearsley)", "duration": 84637, "language": "English", "authors": [{"id": "5771", "name": " Cornelius Beringer"}, {"id": "6384", "name": "John Jacob Beringer"}], "coverArt": "https://archive.org/download/LibrivoxCdCoverArt13/Text-book_Assaying_1603.jpg", "copyright_year": "1904", "genres": ["Earth Sciences"], "supporters": [{"role": "Read by", "name": "Peter Yearsley"}, {"role": "Book Coordinator", "name": "Peter Yearsley"}, {"role": "Meta Coordinator", "name": "Laurie Anne Walden"}, {"role": "Proof Listener", "name": "janbbeck"}], "sections": [{"section": 1, "title": "Ch 1 - Introductory", "readers": [167], "path": "http://www.archive.org/download/textbookassaying_1603_librivox/textbookassaying_01_beringer_64kb.mp3", "duration": 2155}, {"section": 2, "title": "Ch 2 - Dry Gravimetric Methods", "readers": [167], "path": "http://www.archive.org/download/textbookassaying_160